MKHULU Eugene van Tonder appeared in court on Friday, 27 January, for illegal possession of firearms and ammunition. The Secunda Magistrates Court in Mpumalanga postponed his bail application and he will be kept in jail until 2 February. He was arrested by the Hawks, Crime Intelligence and the Secunda K9 Unit on Thursday, 26 January. Provincial Hawks spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Philani Nkwalase said the team responded to a tip-off about illegal firearms and ammunition. “They proceeded to the identified address in Secunda and upon arrival, the suspect was found at his place of residence,” he said. “A search was conducted and inside the house a CZ 75B pistol, 32 Bernadelli pistol, a blank gun and 9mm, 32 special and 12 gauge ammunition were found. “Members also found a bag containing about 1kg of platinum powder. “The firearms were tested and one was found to have been stolen during an armed robbery in Boksburg in 2005, while the other belonged to a person who died in 2011.” Meanwhile, in a separate matter, Frans Nkadimeng (37) appeared in the Middelburg Magistrates Court on Friday on charges of fraudfor using a fraudulent bank statement and payslips to apply for car finance in May last year. You must be SIGNED IN to comment! Nkwalase said: “The “The application for a 2017 VW T6 Kombi 2.0 valued at R570 885 submitted at a dealership in Middelburg was approved and thsuspect took delivery of the vehicle and never made any payments.” ,” he said. He said the suspect was traced and arrested in possession of the vehicle by the Hawks on Wednesday 25 January in Joburg.The matter will be heard in court again on 10 February.